to the editor the wrongful imprisonment of kerry sanders a man with a history of mental health problems has implications beyond his tragic personal loss of freedom and dignity and the obvious folly of the criminal justice system editorial aug 20 it is a statement about how our country treats many of its most vulnerable citizens the seriously mentally ill more than 265000 of the country 's mentally ill are now in prison while only 70000 receive hospital based care in public facilities the correctional system has become the biggest psychiatric hospital in the world people who suffer from mental illness deserve the community based treatment they were promised as well as clean modern hospitals when needed the misfortune of kerry sanders should serve notice on the public mental health and criminal justice systems robert n davison executive director mental health association of essex county montclair nj aug 20 2000

